rComments: Highly recommend this class if you are in french immersion, it was easier than other french health sci courses. Prof East is super nice and answers emails. Just note he will do the entire 3 hours of lecture but I didn't really have to attend and still did well. No textbook, mostly PPT and videos/movies. There is a midterm, journal, exam.

I really liked this class, but the course load was quite heavy. We had a midterm, a final, a weekly journal, and a number of assignments based on videos to complete before the following class. Still, the material was interesting, and the assignments and tests were very fair! East is also such a nice person, but his 3-hour lectures are lengthy.

This class is fun. There are tons of movies to watch in class. The exams are very straight forward no surprises. If you go to class and take notes you cannot fail this class. The prof is very caring and wants everyones success.
